47#define MEMOPSIZE_OF(datasize) ((datasize == 8 || datasize == 128) ? MemOpSize_8_or_128 : (datasize == 16) ? MemOpSize_16 : (datasize == 32) ? MemOpSize_32 : MemOpSize_64)

59template<size_t bits, typename Type>
60ALWAYS_INLINE constexpr bool isInt(Type t)
61{
62 constexpr size_t shift = sizeof(Type) * CHAR_BIT - bits;
63 static_assert(sizeof(Type) * CHAR_BIT > shift, "shift is larger than the size of the value");
64 return ((t << shift) >> shift) == t;
65}

67static ALWAYS_INLINE bool is4ByteAligned(const void* ptr)
68{
69 return !(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(ptr) & 0x3);
70}

72ALWAYS_INLINE bool isUInt5(int32_t value)
73{
74 return !(value & ~0x1f);
75}

188// ARM64 always has 32 FPU registers 128-bits each. See http://llvm.org/devmtg/2012-11/Northover-AArch64.pdf
189// and Section 5.1.2 in http://infocenter.arm.com/help/topic/com.arm.doc.ihi0055b/IHI0055B_aapcs64.pdf.
190// However, we only use them for 64-bit doubles.
191typedef enum : int8_t {
192#define REGISTER_ID(id, name, r, cs) id,
193 FOR_EACH_FP_REGISTER(REGISTER_ID)
194#undef REGISTER_ID
195 InvalidFPRReg = -1,
196} FPRegisterID;

198static constexpr bool isSp(RegisterID reg) { return reg == sp; }
199static constexpr bool isZr(RegisterID reg) { return reg == zr; }

211 static constexpr RegisterID firstRegister() { return ARM64Registers::x0; }
212 static constexpr RegisterID lastRegister() { return ARM64Registers::sp; }
213 static constexpr unsigned numberOfRegisters() { return lastRegister() - firstRegister() + 1; }
214
215 static constexpr SPRegisterID firstSPRegister() { return ARM64Registers::pc; }
216 static constexpr SPRegisterID lastSPRegister() { return ARM64Registers::fpsr; }
217 static constexpr unsigned numberOfSPRegisters() { return lastSPRegister() - firstSPRegister() + 1; }
218
219 static constexpr FPRegisterID firstFPRegister() { return ARM64Registers::q0; }
220 static constexpr FPRegisterID lastFPRegister() { return ARM64Registers::q31; }
221 static constexpr unsigned numberOfFPRegisters() { return lastFPRegister() - firstFPRegister() + 1; }
222
223 static const char* gprName(RegisterID id)
224 {
225 ASSERT(id >= firstRegister() && id <= lastRegister());
226 static const char* const nameForRegister[numberOfRegisters()] = {
227#define REGISTER_NAME(id, name, r, cs) name,
228 FOR_EACH_GP_REGISTER(REGISTER_NAME)
229#undef REGISTER_NAME
230 };
231 return nameForRegister[id];
232 }
233
234 static const char* sprName(SPRegisterID id)
235 {
236 ASSERT(id >= firstSPRegister() && id <= lastSPRegister());
237 static const char* const nameForRegister[numberOfSPRegisters()] = {
238#define REGISTER_NAME(id, name) name,
239 FOR_EACH_SP_REGISTER(REGISTER_NAME)
240#undef REGISTER_NAME
241 };
242 return nameForRegister[id];
243 }
244
245 static const char* fprName(FPRegisterID id)
246 {
247 ASSERT(id >= firstFPRegister() && id <= lastFPRegister());
248 static const char* const nameForRegister[numberOfFPRegisters()] = {
249#define REGISTER_NAME(id, name, r, cs) name,
250 FOR_EACH_FP_REGISTER(REGISTER_NAME)
251#undef REGISTER_NAME
252 };
253 return nameForRegister[id];
254 }

322 JumpCondition = JUMP_ENUM_WITH_SIZE(2, 2 * sizeof(uint32_t)),
323 JumpCompareAndBranch = JUMP_ENUM_WITH_SIZE(3, 2 * sizeof(uint32_t)),
324 JumpTestBit = JUMP_ENUM_WITH_SIZE(4, 2 * sizeof(uint32_t)),

326 JumpConditionFixedSize = JUMP_ENUM_WITH_SIZE(6, 2 * sizeof(uint32_t)),
327 JumpCompareAndBranchFixedSize = JUMP_ENUM_WITH_SIZE(7, 2 * sizeof(uint32_t)),
328 JumpTestBitFixedSize = JUMP_ENUM_WITH_SIZE(8, 2 * sizeof(uint32_t)),
329 };

343 LinkRecord(const ARM64Assembler* assembler, intptr_t from, intptr_t to, JumpType type, Condition condition)
344 {
345 data.realTypes.m_from = from;
346#if CPU(ARM64E)
347 data.realTypes.m_to = tagInt(to, static_cast<PtrTag>(from ^ bitwise_cast<intptr_t>(assembler)));
348#else
349 UNUSED_PARAM(assembler);
350 data.realTypes.m_to = to;
351#endif
352 data.realTypes.m_type = type;
353 data.realTypes.m_linkType = LinkInvalid;
354 data.realTypes.m_condition = condition;
355 }
356 LinkRecord(const ARM64Assembler* assembler, intptr_t from, intptr_t to, JumpType type, Condition condition, bool is64Bit, RegisterID compareRegister)
357 {
358 data.realTypes.m_from = from;
359#if CPU(ARM64E)
360 data.realTypes.m_to = tagInt(to, static_cast<PtrTag>(from ^ bitwise_cast<intptr_t>(assembler)));
361#else
362 UNUSED_PARAM(assembler);
363 data.realTypes.m_to = to;
364#endif
365 data.realTypes.m_type = type;
366 data.realTypes.m_linkType = LinkInvalid;
367 data.realTypes.m_condition = condition;
368 data.realTypes.m_is64Bit = is64Bit;
369 data.realTypes.m_compareRegister = compareRegister;
370 }
371 LinkRecord(const ARM64Assembler* assembler, intptr_t from, intptr_t to, JumpType type, Condition condition, unsigned bitNumber, RegisterID compareRegister)
372 {
373 data.realTypes.m_from = from;
374#if CPU(ARM64E)
375 data.realTypes.m_to = tagInt(to, static_cast<PtrTag>(from ^ bitwise_cast<intptr_t>(assembler)));
376#else
377 UNUSED_PARAM(assembler);
378 data.realTypes.m_to = to;
379#endif
380 data.realTypes.m_type = type;
381 data.realTypes.m_linkType = LinkInvalid;
382 data.realTypes.m_condition = condition;
383 data.realTypes.m_bitNumber = bitNumber;
384 data.realTypes.m_compareRegister = compareRegister;
385 }
386 // We are defining a copy constructor and assignment operator
387 // because the ones provided by the compiler are not
388 // optimal. See https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=90930
389 LinkRecord(const LinkRecord& other)
390 {
391 data.copyTypes = other.data.copyTypes;
392 }
393 LinkRecord& operator=(const LinkRecord& other)
394 {
395 data.copyTypes = other.data.copyTypes;
396 return *this;
397 }
398 intptr_t from() const { return data.realTypes.m_from; }
399 void setFrom(const ARM64Assembler* assembler, intptr_t from)
400 {
401#if CPU(ARM64E)
402 data.realTypes.m_to = tagInt(to(assembler), static_cast<PtrTag>(from ^ bitwise_cast<intptr_t>(assembler)));
403#else
404 UNUSED_PARAM(assembler);
405#endif
406 data.realTypes.m_from = from;
407 }
408 intptr_t to(const ARM64Assembler* assembler) const
409 {
410#if CPU(ARM64E)
411 return untagInt(data.realTypes.m_to, static_cast<PtrTag>(data.realTypes.m_from ^ bitwise_cast<intptr_t>(assembler)));
412#else
413 UNUSED_PARAM(assembler);
414 return data.realTypes.m_to;
415#endif
416 }
417 JumpType type() const { return data.realTypes.m_type; }
418 JumpLinkType linkType() const { return data.realTypes.m_linkType; }
419 void setLinkType(JumpLinkType linkType) { ASSERT(data.realTypes.m_linkType == LinkInvalid); data.realTypes.m_linkType = linkType; }
420 Condition condition() const { return data.realTypes.m_condition; }
421 bool is64Bit() const { return data.realTypes.m_is64Bit; }
422 unsigned bitNumber() const { return data.realTypes.m_bitNumber; }
423 RegisterID compareRegister() const { return data.realTypes.m_compareRegister; }

437 struct CopyTypes {

439 } copyTypes;
440 COMPILE_ASSERT(sizeof(RealTypes) == sizeof(CopyTypes), LinkRecordCopyStructSizeEqualsRealStruct);
441 } data;

444 // bits(N) VFPExpandImm(bits(8) imm8);
445 //
446 // Encoding of floating point immediates is a litte complicated. Here's a
447 // high level description:
448 // +/-m*2-n where m and n are integers, 16 <= m <= 31, 0 <= n <= 7
449 // and the algirithm for expanding to a single precision float:
450 // return imm8<7>:NOT(imm8<6>):Replicate(imm8<6>,5):imm8<5:0>:Zeros(19);
451 //
452 // The trickiest bit is how the exponent is handled. The following table
453 // may help clarify things a little:
454 // 654
455 // 100 01111100 124 -3 1020 01111111100
456 // 101 01111101 125 -2 1021 01111111101
457 // 110 01111110 126 -1 1022 01111111110
458 // 111 01111111 127 0 1023 01111111111
459 // 000 10000000 128 1 1024 10000000000
460 // 001 10000001 129 2 1025 10000000001
461 // 010 10000010 130 3 1026 10000000010
462 // 011 10000011 131 4 1027 10000000011
463 // The first column shows the bit pattern stored in bits 6-4 of the arm
464 // encoded immediate. The second column shows the 8-bit IEEE 754 single
465 // -precision exponent in binary, the third column shows the raw decimal
466 // value. IEEE 754 single-precision numbers are stored with a bias of 127
467 // to the exponent, so the fourth column shows the resulting exponent.
468 // From this was can see that the exponent can be in the range -3..4,
469 // which agrees with the high level description given above. The fifth
470 // and sixth columns shows the value stored in a IEEE 754 double-precision
471 // number to represent these exponents in decimal and binary, given the
472 // bias of 1023.
473 //
474 // Ultimately, detecting doubles that can be encoded as immediates on arm
475 // and encoding doubles is actually not too bad. A floating point value can
476 // be encoded by retaining the sign bit, the low three bits of the exponent
477 // and the high 4 bits of the mantissa. To validly be able to encode an
478 // immediate the remainder of the mantissa must be zero, and the high part
479 // of the exponent must match the top bit retained, bar the highest bit
480 // which must be its inverse.
481 static bool canEncodeFPImm(double d)
482 {
483 // Discard the sign bit, the low two bits of the exponent & the highest
484 // four bits of the mantissa.
485 uint64_t masked = bitwise_cast<uint64_t>(d) & 0x7fc0ffffffffffffull;
486 return (masked == 0x3fc0000000000000ull) || (masked == 0x4000000000000000ull);
487 }
488
489 template<int datasize>
490 static bool canEncodePImmOffset(int32_t offset)
491 {
492 return isValidScaledUImm12<datasize>(offset);
493 }
494
495 static bool canEncodeSImmOffset(int32_t offset)
496 {
497 return isValidSignedImm9(offset);
498 }
499
500protected:
501 int encodeFPImm(double d)
502 {
503 ASSERT(canEncodeFPImm(d));
504 uint64_t u64 = bitwise_cast<uint64_t>(d);
505 return (static_cast<int>(u64 >> 56) & 0x80) | (static_cast<int>(u64 >> 48) & 0x7f);
506 }

508 template<int datasize>
509 int encodeShiftAmount(int amount)
510 {
511 ASSERT(!amount || datasize == (8 << amount));
512 return amount;
513 }
514
515 template<int datasize>
516 static int encodePositiveImmediate(unsigned pimm)
517 {
518 ASSERT(!(pimm & ((datasize / 8) - 1)));
519 return pimm / (datasize / 8);
520 }

720 static unsigned memPairOffsetShift(bool V, MemPairOpSize size)
721 {
722 // return the log2 of the size in bytes, e.g. 64 bit size returns 3
723 if (V)
724 return size + 2;
725 return (size >> 1) + 2;
726 }

893 ALWAYS_INLINE static bool isBrk(void* address)
894 {
895 int expected = excepnGeneration(ExcepnOp_BREAKPOINT, 0, 0);
896 int immediateMask = excepnGenerationImmMask();

898 return (candidateInstruction & ~immediateMask) == expected;

1569 ALWAYS_INLINE void nop()
1570 {
1571 insn(nopPseudo());
1572 }
1573
1574 enum BranchTargetType { DirectBranch, IndirectBranch };
1575 using CopyFunction = void*(&)(void*, const void*, size_t);
1576
1577 template <CopyFunction copy>
1578 ALWAYS_INLINE static void fillNops(void* base, size_t size)
1579 {
1580 RELEASE_ASSERT(!(size % sizeof(int32_t)));
1581 size_t n = size / sizeof(int32_t);
1582 for (int32_t* ptr = static_cast<int32_t*>(base); n--;) {
1583 int insn = nopPseudo();
1584 RELEASE_ASSERT(roundUpToMultipleOf<instructionSize>(ptr) == ptr);
1585 copy(ptr++, &insn, sizeof(int));
1586 }
1587 }

1974 template<int datasize, SetFlags setFlags = DontSetFlags>
1975 ALWAYS_INLINE void sub(RegisterID rd, RegisterID rn, RegisterID rm)
1976 {
1977 ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE(!isSp(rd) || setFlags == DontSetFlags, "SUBS with shifted register does not support SP for Xd, it uses XZR for the register 31. SUBS with extended register support SP for Xd, but only if SetFlag is not used, otherwise register 31 is Xd.");
1978 ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE(!isSp(rm), "No encoding of SUBS supports SP for the third operand.");
1979
1980 if (isSp(rd) || isSp(rn))
1981 sub<datasize, setFlags>(rd, rn, rm, UXTX, 0);
1982 else
1983 sub<datasize, setFlags>(rd, rn, rm, LSL, 0);
1984 }

2694 static void replaceWithJump(void* where, void* to)
2695 {

2735 ASSERT(!S);
2736 ASSERT(!shift);

2744 else {
2745 MemOpSize size;
2746 bool V;
2747 MemOp opc;
2748 int imm12;
2749 RegisterID rn;
2750 RegisterID rt;
2751 ASSERT(disassembleLoadStoreRegisterUnsignedImmediate(where, size, V, opc, imm12, rn, rt));
2752 ASSERT(size == MemOpSize_64);

2802 static void setPointer(int* address, void* valuePtr, RegisterID rd, bool flush)
2803 {
2804 uintptr_t value = reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(valuePtr);
2805 int buffer[3];
2806 buffer[0] = moveWideImediate(Datasize_64, MoveWideOp_Z, 0, getHalfword(value, 0), rd);
2807 buffer[1] = moveWideImediate(Datasize_64, MoveWideOp_K, 1, getHalfword(value, 1), rd);
2808 buffer[2] = moveWideImediate(Datasize_64, MoveWideOp_K, 2, getHalfword(value, 2), rd);
2809 RELEASE_ASSERT(roundUpToMultipleOf<instructionSize>(address) == address);
2810 performJITMemcpy(address, buffer, sizeof(int) * 3);
2811
2812 if (flush)
2813 cacheFlush(address, sizeof(int) * 3);
2814 }

2816 static void repatchInt32(void* where, int32_t value)
2817 {
2818 int* address = static_cast<int*>(where);
2819
2820 Datasize sf;
2821 MoveWideOp opc;
2822 int hw;
2823 uint16_t imm16;
2824 RegisterID rd;
2825 bool expected = disassembleMoveWideImediate(address, sf, opc, hw, imm16, rd);
2826 ASSERT_UNUSED(expected, expected && !sf && (opc == MoveWideOp_Z || opc == MoveWideOp_N) && !hw);
2827 ASSERT(checkMovk<Datasize_32>(address[1], 1, rd));
2828
2829 int buffer[2];
2830 if (value >= 0) {
2831 buffer[0] = moveWideImediate(Datasize_32, MoveWideOp_Z, 0, getHalfword(value, 0), rd);
2832 buffer[1] = moveWideImediate(Datasize_32, MoveWideOp_K, 1, getHalfword(value, 1), rd);
2833 } else {
2834 buffer[0] = moveWideImediate(Datasize_32, MoveWideOp_N, 0, ~getHalfword(value, 0), rd);
2835 buffer[1] = moveWideImediate(Datasize_32, MoveWideOp_K, 1, getHalfword(value, 1), rd);
2836 }
2837 RELEASE_ASSERT(roundUpToMultipleOf<instructionSize>(where) == where);
2838 performJITMemcpy(where, &buffer, sizeof(int) * 2);
2839
2840 cacheFlush(where, sizeof(int) * 2);
2841 }
2842
2843 static void* readPointer(void* where)
2844 {
2845 int* address = static_cast<int*>(where);
2846
2847 Datasize sf;
2848 MoveWideOp opc;
2849 int hw;
2850 uint16_t imm16;
2851 RegisterID rdFirst, rd;
2852
2853 bool expected = disassembleMoveWideImediate(address, sf, opc, hw, imm16, rdFirst);
2854 ASSERT_UNUSED(expected, expected && sf && opc == MoveWideOp_Z && !hw);
2855 uintptr_t result = imm16;
2856
2857 expected = disassembleMoveWideImediate(address + 1, sf, opc, hw, imm16, rd);
2858 ASSERT_UNUSED(expected, expected && sf && opc == MoveWideOp_K && hw == 1 && rd == rdFirst);
2859 result |= static_cast<uintptr_t>(imm16) << 16;
2860
2861#if CPU(ADDRESS64)
2862 expected = disassembleMoveWideImediate(address + 2, sf, opc, hw, imm16, rd);
2863 ASSERT_UNUSED(expected, expected && sf && opc == MoveWideOp_K && hw == 2 && rd == rdFirst);
2864 result |= static_cast<uintptr_t>(imm16) << 32;
2865#endif
2866
2867 return reinterpret_cast<void*>(result);
2868 }

2916 static void repatchCompact(void* where, int32_t value)
2917 {
2918 ASSERT(!(value & ~0x3ff8));
2919
2920 MemOpSize size;
2921 bool V;
2922 MemOp opc;
2923 int imm12;
2924 RegisterID rn;
2925 RegisterID rt;
2926 bool expected = disassembleLoadStoreRegisterUnsignedImmediate(where, size, V, opc, imm12, rn, rt);
2927 ASSERT_UNUSED(expected, expected && size >= MemOpSize_32 && !V && opc == MemOp_LOAD); // expect 32/64 bit load to GPR.
2928
2929 if (size == MemOpSize_32)
2930 imm12 = encodePositiveImmediate<32>(value);
2931 else
2932 imm12 = encodePositiveImmediate<64>(value);
2933 int insn = loadStoreRegisterUnsignedImmediate(size, V, opc, imm12, rn, rt);
2934 RELEASE_ASSERT(roundUpToMultipleOf<instructionSize>(where) == where);
2935 performJITMemcpy(where, &insn, sizeof(int));
2936
2937 cacheFlush(where, sizeof(int));
2938 }

2942#if OS(LINUX) && COMPILER(GCC_COMPATIBLE)
2943 static inline void linuxPageFlush(uintptr_t begin, uintptr_t end)
2944 {
2945 __builtin___clear_cache(reinterpret_cast<char*>(begin), reinterpret_cast<char*>(end));
2946 }
2947#endif
2948
2949 static void cacheFlush(void* code, size_t size)
2950 {
2951#if OS(DARWIN)
2952 sys_cache_control(kCacheFunctionPrepareForExecution, code, size);
2953#elif OS(FUCHSIA)
2954 zx_cache_flush(code, size, ZX_CACHE_FLUSH_INSN);
2955#elif OS(LINUX)
2956 size_t page = pageSize();
2957 uintptr_t current = reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(code);
2958 uintptr_t end = current + size;
2959 uintptr_t firstPageEnd = (current & ~(page - 1)) + page;
2960
2961 if (end <= firstPageEnd) {
2962 linuxPageFlush(current, end);
2963 return;
2964 }
2965
2966 linuxPageFlush(current, firstPageEnd);
2967
2968 for (current = firstPageEnd; current + page < end; current += page)
2969 linuxPageFlush(current, current + page);
2970
2971 linuxPageFlush(current, end);
2972#else
2973#error "The cacheFlush support is missing on this platform."
2974#endif
2975 }

2982 {

2984 }
2985
2986 static bool canCompact(JumpType jumpType)
2987 {
2988 // Fixed jumps cannot be compacted
2989 return (jumpType == JumpNoCondition) || (jumpType == JumpCondition) || (jumpType == JumpCompareAndBranch) || (jumpType == JumpTestBit);
2990 }
2991
2992 static JumpLinkType computeJumpType(JumpType jumpType, const uint8_t* from, const uint8_t* to)
2993 {
2994 switch (jumpType) {
2995 case JumpFixed:
2996 return LinkInvalid;
2997 case JumpNoConditionFixedSize:
2998 return LinkJumpNoCondition;
2999 case JumpConditionFixedSize:
3000 return LinkJumpCondition;
3001 case JumpCompareAndBranchFixedSize:
3002 return LinkJumpCompareAndBranch;
3003 case JumpTestBitFixedSize:
3004 return LinkJumpTestBit;
3005 case JumpNoCondition:
3006 return LinkJumpNoCondition;
3007 case JumpCondition: {
3008 ASSERT(is4ByteAligned(from));
3009 ASSERT(is4ByteAligned(to));
3010 intptr_t relative = reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(to) - (reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(from));
3011
3012 if (isInt<21>(relative))
3013 return LinkJumpConditionDirect;
3014
3015 return LinkJumpCondition;
3016 }
3017 case JumpCompareAndBranch: {
3018 ASSERT(is4ByteAligned(from));
3019 ASSERT(is4ByteAligned(to));
3020 intptr_t relative = reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(to) - (reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(from));
3021
3022 if (isInt<21>(relative))
3023 return LinkJumpCompareAndBranchDirect;
3024
3025 return LinkJumpCompareAndBranch;
3026 }
3027 case JumpTestBit: {
3028 ASSERT(is4ByteAligned(from));
3029 ASSERT(is4ByteAligned(to));
3030 intptr_t relative = reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(to) - (reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(from));
3031
3032 if (isInt<14>(relative))
3033 return LinkJumpTestBitDirect;
3034
3035 return LinkJumpTestBit;
3036 }
3037 default:
3038 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
3039 }
3040
3041 return LinkJumpNoCondition;
3042 }
3043
3044 static JumpLinkType computeJumpType(LinkRecord& record, const uint8_t* from, const uint8_t* to)
3045 {
3046 JumpLinkType linkType = computeJumpType(record.type(), from, to);
3047 record.setLinkType(linkType);
3048 return linkType;
3049 }
3050
3051 Vector<LinkRecord, 0, UnsafeVectorOverflow>& jumpsToLink()
3052 {
3053 std::sort(m_jumpsToLink.begin(), m_jumpsToLink.end(), linkRecordSourceComparator);
3054 return m_jumpsToLink;
3055 }
3056
3057 template<CopyFunction copy>
3058 static void ALWAYS_INLINE link(LinkRecord& record, uint8_t* from, const uint8_t* fromInstruction8, uint8_t* to)
3059 {
3060 const int* fromInstruction = reinterpret_cast<const int*>(fromInstruction8);
3061 switch (record.linkType()) {
3062 case LinkJumpNoCondition:
3063 linkJumpOrCall<BranchType_JMP, copy>(reinterpret_cast<int*>(from), fromInstruction, to);
3064 break;
3065 case LinkJumpConditionDirect:
3066 linkConditionalBranch<DirectBranch, copy>(record.condition(), reinterpret_cast<int*>(from), fromInstruction, to);
3067 break;
3068 case LinkJumpCondition:
3069 linkConditionalBranch<IndirectBranch, copy>(record.condition(), reinterpret_cast<int*>(from) - 1, fromInstruction - 1, to);
3070 break;
3071 case LinkJumpCompareAndBranchDirect:
3072 linkCompareAndBranch<DirectBranch, copy>(record.condition(), record.is64Bit(), record.compareRegister(), reinterpret_cast<int*>(from), fromInstruction, to);
3073 break;
3074 case LinkJumpCompareAndBranch:
3075 linkCompareAndBranch<IndirectBranch, copy>(record.condition(), record.is64Bit(), record.compareRegister(), reinterpret_cast<int*>(from) - 1, fromInstruction - 1, to);
3076 break;
3077 case LinkJumpTestBitDirect:
3078 linkTestAndBranch<DirectBranch, copy>(record.condition(), record.bitNumber(), record.compareRegister(), reinterpret_cast<int*>(from), fromInstruction, to);
3079 break;
3080 case LinkJumpTestBit:
3081 linkTestAndBranch<IndirectBranch, copy>(record.condition(), record.bitNumber(), record.compareRegister(), reinterpret_cast<int*>(from) - 1, fromInstruction - 1, to);
3082 break;
3083 default:
3084 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
3085 break;
3086 }
3087 }

3090 {

3092 return isInt<26>(diff);

3128 template<BranchType type, CopyFunction copy = performJITMemcpy>
3129 static void linkJumpOrCall(int* from, const int* fromInstruction, void* to)
3130 {
3131 static_assert(type == BranchType_JMP || type == BranchType_CALL, "");
3132
3133 bool link;
3134 int imm26;
3135 bool isUnconditionalBranchImmediateOrNop = disassembleUnconditionalBranchImmediate(from, link, imm26) || disassembleNop(from);
3136
3137 ASSERT_UNUSED(isUnconditionalBranchImmediateOrNop, isUnconditionalBranchImmediateOrNop);
3138 constexpr bool isCall = (type == BranchType_CALL);
3139 ASSERT_UNUSED(isCall, (link == isCall) || disassembleNop(from));
3140 ASSERT(!(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(from) & 3));
3141 ASSERT(!(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(to) & 3));
3142 assertIsNotTagged(to);
3143 assertIsNotTagged(fromInstruction);
3144 intptr_t offset = (bitwise_cast<intptr_t>(to) - bitwise_cast<intptr_t>(fromInstruction)) >> 2;
3145 ASSERT(static_cast<int>(offset) == offset);
3146
3147#if ENABLE(JUMP_ISLANDS)
3148 if (!isInt<26>(offset)) {
3149 to = ExecutableAllocator::singleton().getJumpIslandTo(bitwise_cast<void*>(fromInstruction), to);
3150 offset = (bitwise_cast<intptr_t>(to) - bitwise_cast<intptr_t>(fromInstruction)) >> 2;
3151 RELEASE_ASSERT(isInt<26>(offset));
3152 }
3153#endif
3154
3155 int insn = unconditionalBranchImmediate(isCall, static_cast<int>(offset));
3156 RELEASE_ASSERT(roundUpToMultipleOf<instructionSize>(from) == from);
3157 copy(from, &insn, sizeof(int));
3158 }

3160 template<BranchTargetType type, CopyFunction copy = performJITMemcpy>
3161 static void linkCompareAndBranch(Condition condition, bool is64Bit, RegisterID rt, int* from, const int* fromInstruction, void* to)
3162 {
3163 ASSERT(!(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(from) & 3));
3164 ASSERT(!(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(to) & 3));
3165 intptr_t offset = (reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(to) - reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(fromInstruction)) >> 2;
3166
3167 bool useDirect = isInt<19>(offset);
3168 ASSERT(type == IndirectBranch || useDirect);
3169
3170 if (useDirect || type == DirectBranch) {
3171 ASSERT(isInt<19>(offset));
3172 int insn = compareAndBranchImmediate(is64Bit ? Datasize_64 : Datasize_32, condition == ConditionNE, static_cast<int>(offset), rt);
3173 RELEASE_ASSERT(roundUpToMultipleOf<instructionSize>(from) == from);
3174 copy(from, &insn, sizeof(int));
3175 if (type == IndirectBranch) {
3176 insn = nopPseudo();
3177 RELEASE_ASSERT(roundUpToMultipleOf<instructionSize>(from + 1) == (from + 1));
3178 copy(from + 1, &insn, sizeof(int));
3179 }
3180 } else {
3181 int insn = compareAndBranchImmediate(is64Bit ? Datasize_64 : Datasize_32, invert(condition) == ConditionNE, 2, rt);
3182 RELEASE_ASSERT(roundUpToMultipleOf<instructionSize>(from) == from);
3183 copy(from, &insn, sizeof(int));
3184 linkJumpOrCall<BranchType_JMP, copy>(from + 1, fromInstruction + 1, to);
3185 }
3186 }

3188 template<BranchTargetType type, CopyFunction copy = performJITMemcpy>
3189 static void linkConditionalBranch(Condition condition, int* from, const int* fromInstruction, void* to)
3190 {
3191 ASSERT(!(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(from) & 3));
3192 ASSERT(!(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(to) & 3));
3193 intptr_t offset = (reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(to) - reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(fromInstruction)) >> 2;
3194
3195 bool useDirect = isInt<19>(offset);
3196 ASSERT(type == IndirectBranch || useDirect);
3197
3198 if (useDirect || type == DirectBranch) {
3199 ASSERT(isInt<19>(offset));
3200 int insn = conditionalBranchImmediate(static_cast<int>(offset), condition);
3201 RELEASE_ASSERT(roundUpToMultipleOf<instructionSize>(from) == from);
3202 copy(from, &insn, sizeof(int));
3203 if (type == IndirectBranch) {
3204 insn = nopPseudo();
3205 RELEASE_ASSERT(roundUpToMultipleOf<instructionSize>(from + 1) == (from + 1));
3206 copy(from + 1, &insn, sizeof(int));
3207 }
3208 } else {
3209 int insn = conditionalBranchImmediate(2, invert(condition));
3210 RELEASE_ASSERT(roundUpToMultipleOf<instructionSize>(from) == from);
3211 copy(from, &insn, sizeof(int));
3212 linkJumpOrCall<BranchType_JMP, copy>(from + 1, fromInstruction + 1, to);
3213 }

3216 template<BranchTargetType type, CopyFunction copy = performJITMemcpy>
3217 static void linkTestAndBranch(Condition condition, unsigned bitNumber, RegisterID rt, int* from, const int* fromInstruction, void* to)
3218 {
3219 ASSERT(!(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(from) & 3));
3220 ASSERT(!(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(to) & 3));
3221 intptr_t offset = (reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(to) - reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(fromInstruction)) >> 2;
3222 ASSERT(static_cast<int>(offset) == offset);
3223
3224 bool useDirect = isInt<14>(offset);
3225 ASSERT(type == IndirectBranch || useDirect);
3226
3227 if (useDirect || type == DirectBranch) {
3228 ASSERT(isInt<14>(offset));
3229 int insn = testAndBranchImmediate(condition == ConditionNE, static_cast<int>(bitNumber), static_cast<int>(offset), rt);
3230 RELEASE_ASSERT(roundUpToMultipleOf<instructionSize>(from) == from);
3231 copy(from, &insn, sizeof(int));
3232 if (type == IndirectBranch) {
3233 insn = nopPseudo();
3234 RELEASE_ASSERT(roundUpToMultipleOf<instructionSize>(from + 1) == (from + 1));
3235 copy(from + 1, &insn, sizeof(int));
3236 }
3237 } else {
3238 int insn = testAndBranchImmediate(invert(condition) == ConditionNE, static_cast<int>(bitNumber), 2, rt);
3239 RELEASE_ASSERT(roundUpToMultipleOf<instructionSize>(from) == from);
3240 copy(from, &insn, sizeof(int));

3245 template<BranchType type>
3246 static void relinkJumpOrCall(int* from, const int* fromInstruction, void* to)
3247 {
3248 static_assert(type == BranchType_JMP || type == BranchType_CALL, "");
3249 if ((type == BranchType_JMP) && disassembleNop(from)) {
3250 unsigned op01;
3251 int imm19;
3252 Condition condition;
3253 bool isConditionalBranchImmediate = disassembleConditionalBranchImmediate(from - 1, op01, imm19, condition);
3254
3255 if (isConditionalBranchImmediate) {
3256 ASSERT_UNUSED(op01, !op01);
3257 ASSERT(type == BranchType_JMP);
3258
3259 if (imm19 == 8)
3260 condition = invert(condition);
3261
3262 linkConditionalBranch<IndirectBranch>(condition, from - 1, fromInstruction - 1, to);
3263 return;
3264 }
3265
3266 Datasize opSize;
3267 bool op;
3268 RegisterID rt;
3269 bool isCompareAndBranchImmediate = disassembleCompareAndBranchImmediate(from - 1, opSize, op, imm19, rt);
3270
3271 if (isCompareAndBranchImmediate) {
3272 if (imm19 == 8)
3273 op = !op;
3274
3275 linkCompareAndBranch<IndirectBranch>(op ? ConditionNE : ConditionEQ, opSize == Datasize_64, rt, from - 1, fromInstruction - 1, to);
3276 return;
3277 }
3278
3279 int imm14;
3280 unsigned bitNumber;
3281 bool isTestAndBranchImmediate = disassembleTestAndBranchImmediate(from - 1, op, bitNumber, imm14, rt);
3282
3283 if (isTestAndBranchImmediate) {
3284 if (imm14 == 8)
3285 op = !op;
3286
3287 linkTestAndBranch<IndirectBranch>(op ? ConditionNE : ConditionEQ, bitNumber, rt, from - 1, fromInstruction - 1, to);
3288 return;
3289 }
3290 }
3291
3292 linkJumpOrCall<type>(from, fromInstruction, to);
3293 }
